  "instructions": [
    "Prepare the marinade by mixing yogurt, ginger garlic paste, salt, garam masala, turmeric, lemon juice, and red chili powder.",
    "Marinate the chicken with this mixture and let it rest overnight.",
    "Rinse the basmati rice 3 times (until water is clear) and soak for 30 minutes.",
    "In a dutch oven, heat ghee and sauté whole spices until they start to sizzle.",
    "Add onions and fry until light brown.",
    "Add the marinated chicken and sauté until tender (about 5 minutes)",
    "Cover and cook until the chicken is tender, ensuring any excess moisture evaporates.",
    "Add the .25 cups of yogurt, .25 cups of mint leaves, jalepeno, red chili powder, and garam masala. Mix and make sure everything is levelled.",
    "Layer the basmati rice over the chicken.",
    "If necessary, add salted water until the rice is covered by about 2 cm, sprinkle with mint leaves, and cook covered on medium until the rice is perfectly cooked."
  ]
